     3→//!
     4→//! Pagination-aware, type-safe Redis cache for “Query” side of the
     5→//! Command/Query separation used by LedgerLink Nexus.  The cache is designed
     6→//! to work in a multi-tenant, horizontally-scaled micro-service and therefore
     7→//! supports:
     8→//!   • namespaced keys (tenant isolation)
     9→//!   • expirations / soft TTL
    10→//!   • pub/sub-based fan-out invalidation
    11→//!   • structured tracing and metrics
    12→//!
    13→//! The public API intentionally mimics an ordinary repository call so the
    14→//! surrounding service layer can stay oblivious to the actual caching
    15→//! strategy.
    16→//!
    17→//! # Example
    18→//! ```no_run
    19→//! # use uuid::Uuid;
    20→//! # use ledgerlink_nexus::cache::{PagedCache, Pagination, CacheableQuery};
    21→//! # use tokio::runtime::Runtime;
    22→//! #
    23→//! #[derive(Clone, Debug)]
    24→//! struct GetLedgerEntryPage {
    25→//!     pub tenant_id: Uuid,
    26→//!     pub account_id: Uuid,
    27→//!     pub pagination: Pagination,
    28→//! }
